UNITED STATES of America, Appellee v. Lonnell GLOVER, Appellant No. 16-3001

September Term, 2016

United States Court of Appeals, District of Columbia Circuit. Filed: 11/23/2016 Zia Mustafa Faruqui, Elizabeth Tros-man, Esquire, Assistant U.S. Attorneys, USAO Appellate Counsel, U.S. Attorney’s Office (USA), Appellate Division, Washington, DC, for Plaintiff-Appellee. David B. Smith, David B. Smith, PLLC, Alexandria, VA, Warden (Washington CDF), Central Detention Facility, DC Prison, Washington, DC, for Defendant-Appellant. Lonnell Glover, Pro Se.

ORDER

Upon consideration of appellant’s notice of dismissal, his motion to dismiss appeal, and the affidavit in support thereof, it is

ORDERED that the motion be granted, and this case be dismissed. See D.C. Circuit Handbook of Practice and Internal Procedures 34-35 (2016).
